{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844790199,"sessionID":"ses_287677128ffe1OYkAXjU0bM6jn","part":{"id":"prt_d78990ba4001H0VkY9g7hnJLXx","messageID":"msg_d7898fea8001AoXsnHKsIEvdxJ","sessionID":"ses_287677128ffe1OYkAXjU0bM6jn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-86af1c59ef054b43bcae89f1c88ee762","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: [待填写: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理概述]\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: [待填写]\n18: \n19: The system SHALL [待填写].\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: [待填写]\n22: - **GIVEN** [待填写]\n23: - **WHEN** [待填写]\n24: - **THEN** [待填写]\n25: \n26: ---\n27: \n28: ## Implementation Files\n29: \n30: | File | Purpose |\n31: |------|---------|\n32: | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n33: \n34: ---\n35: \n36: ## Dependencies\n37: \n38: | Package | Purpose |\n39: |---------|---------|\n40: | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n41: \n42: ---\n43: \n44: ## API Endpoints\n45: \n46: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n47: |----------|--------|---------|\n48: | [待填写] | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## Error Codes\n53: \n54: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n55: |------|-------------|-------------|\n56: | [待填写] | [待填写] | [待填写] |\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## Validation Checklist\n61: \n62: - [ ] [待填写]\n\n(End of file - total 62 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\n[待填写: Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理概述]\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: [待填写]\n\nThe system SHALL [待填写].\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775844790188,"end":1775844790198}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844790203,"sessionID":"ses_287677128ffe1OYkAXjU0bM6jn","part":{"id":"prt_d78990f9200143hsZjujLedRZ6","messageID":"msg_d7898fea8001AoXsnHKsIEvdxJ","sessionID":"ses_287677128ffe1OYkAXjU0bM6jn","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-82fd5aa5df354c3ca5aaf942b5ce8ea9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n2: \n3: **Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n4: **Language:** Go  \n5: **Size:** M\n6: \n7: ---\n8: \n9: ## Overview\n10: \n11: Define the Sandbox creation handler that processes sandbox creation requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including pod creation, session management, status updates, and warm pool handling.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: SandboxHandler type definition\n18: \n19: The system SHALL define `SandboxHandler` as an HTTP handler for sandbox creation operations.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: SandboxHandler struct definition\n22: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n23: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxHandler` struct\n24: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n25:   - `client clientset.Interface` for Kubernetes API access\n26:   - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n27:   - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n28:   - `namespace string` for default namespace\n29: \n30: #### Scenario: NewSandboxHandler constructor\n31: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n32: - **WHEN** calling `NewSandboxHandler(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, logger Logger, namespace string)`\n33: - **THEN** it SHALL return `*SandboxHandler` with all fields initialized\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ### Requirement: Handler registration interface\n38: \n39: The system SHALL implement `Handler` interface for route registration.\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Handler interface implementation\n42: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n43: - **WHEN** examining `SandboxHandler`\n44: - **THEN** it SHALL implement `Register(r chi.Router)` method from `workloadmanager.Handler` interface\n45: \n46: #### Scenario: Register method routes\n47: - **GIVEN** a `SandboxHandler` instance\n48: - **WHEN** calling `Register(r chi.Router)`\n49: - **THEN** it SHALL register the following routes:\n50:   - `POST /api/v1/sandboxes` for sandbox creation\n51:   - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` for sandbox retrieval\n52:   - `DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` for sandbox deletion\n53:   - `GET /api/v1/sandboxes` for sandbox listing\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ### Requirement: CreateSandboxRequest type definition\n58: \n59: The system SHALL define request types for sandbox creation API.\n60: \n61: #### Scenario: CreateSandboxRequest struct definition\n62: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n63: - **WHEN** reading the `CreateSandboxRequest` struct\n64: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n65:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (required)\n66:   - `RuntimeName string` with JSON tag `runtimeName` (required)\n67:   - `RuntimeKind string` with JSON tag `runtimeKind` (required, enum: AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter)\n68:   - `SessionID string` with JSON tag `sessionId` (optional)\n69: \n70: #### Scenario: RuntimeKind validation\n71: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n72: - **WHEN** examining the `RuntimeKind` field\n73: - **THEN** valid values SHALL be `\"AgentRuntime\"` and `\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ### Requirement: SandboxResponse type definition\n78: \n79: The system SHALL define response types for sandbox API.\n80: \n81: #### Scenario: SandboxResponse struct definition\n82: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n83: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxResponse` struct\n84: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n85:   - `Name string` with JSON tag `name`\n86:   - `PodName string` with JSON tag `podName`\n87:   - `Namespace string` with JSON tag `namespace`\n88:   - `Status string` with JSON tag `status`\n89:   - `SessionID string` with JSON tag `sessionId`\n90:   - `CreatedAt time.Time` with JSON tag `createdAt`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: SandboxListResponse struct definition\n93: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n94: - **WHEN** reading the `SandboxListResponse` struct\n95: - **THEN** the struct SHALL contain field `Items []SandboxResponse` with JSON tag `items`\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ### Requirement: Sandbox creation logic\n100: \n101: The system SHALL create Kubernetes Pods based on AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter templates.\n102: \n103: #### Scenario: Retrieve AgentRuntime spec\n104: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"AgentRuntime\"`\n105: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox creation request\n106: - **THEN** `SandboxHandler.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().AgentRuntimes(namespace).Get(ctx, runtimeName, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called to retrieve the AgentRuntime\n107: \n108: #### Scenario: Retrieve CodeInterpreter spec\n109: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"CodeInterpreter\"`\n110: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox creation request\n111: - **THEN** `SandboxHandler.client.RuntimeV1alpha1().CodeInterpreters(namespace).Get(ctx, runtimeName, metav1.GetOptions{})` SHALL be called to retrieve the CodeInterpreter\n112: \n113: #### Scenario: Pod creation from AgentRuntime template\n114: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime spec with `Template *SandboxTemplate`\n115: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n116: - **THEN** the Pod SHALL be created using `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n117: - AND the Pod's `Spec` SHALL be derived from `AgentRuntime.Spec.Template.Spec`\n118: \n119: #### Scenario: Pod creation from CodeInterpreter template\n120: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter spec with `Template *CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate`\n121: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n122: - **THEN** the Pod SHALL be created using `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Create(ctx, pod, metav1.CreateOptions{})`\n123: - AND the Pod's container image SHALL be from `CodeInterpreter.Spec.Template.Image`\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ### Requirement: Label application\n128: \n129: The system SHALL apply required labels to sandbox pods according to shared_types.go constants.\n130: \n131: #### Scenario: Owner runtime label\n132: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n133: - **WHEN** applying labels\n134: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` SHALL be set to the runtime name\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Owner kind label\n137: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n138: - **WHEN** applying labels\n139: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` SHALL be set to `RuntimeKind` value\n140: \n141: #### Scenario: Sandbox type label for AgentRuntime\n142: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for AgentRuntime\n143: - **WHEN** applying labels\n144: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` SHALL be set to `\"agent\"`\n145: \n146: #### Scenario: Sandbox type label for CodeInterpreter\n147: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for CodeInterpreter\n148: - **WHEN** applying labels\n149: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` SHALL be set to `\"code-interpreter\"`\n150: \n151: #### Scenario: Session ID label\n152: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created with `SessionID`\n153: - **WHEN** applying labels\n154: - **THEN** label `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` SHALL be set to the session ID\n155: \n156: #### Scenario: Merge template labels\n157: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with template labels\n158: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n159: - **THEN** template labels SHALL be merged with system labels\n160: - AND system labels SHALL not be overridden by template labels\n161: \n162: ---\n163: \n164: ### Requirement: Annotation application\n165: \n166: The system SHALL apply required annotations to sandbox pods.\n167: \n168: #### Scenario: Session start annotation\n169: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n170: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n171: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` SHALL be set to current timestamp in RFC3339 format\n172: \n173: #### Scenario: Last activity annotation\n174: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created\n175: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n176: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n177: \n178: #### Scenario: Auth mode annotation for CodeInterpreter\n179: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox pod being created\n180: - **WHEN** applying annotations\n181: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` SHALL be set to `CodeInterpreter.Spec.AuthMode`\n182: \n183: #### Scenario: Merge template annotations\n184: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime or CodeInterpreter with template annotations\n185: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n186: - **THEN** template annotations SHALL be merged with system annotations\n187: - AND system annotations SHALL not be overridden by template annotations\n188: \n189: ---\n190: \n191: ### Requirement: Pod naming convention\n192: \n193: The system SHALL generate unique pod names for sandboxes.\n194: \n195: #### Scenario: Pod name format\n196: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `Name=\"my-sandbox\"`\n197: - **WHEN** generating the pod name\n198: - **THEN** the pod name SHALL follow format `{sandbox-name}-{randomSuffix}`\n199: - AND the random suffix SHALL be 5 characters alphanumeric\n200: \n201: #### Scenario: Pod name uniqueness\n202: - **GIVEN** an existing pod with the same sandbox name\n203: - **WHEN** creating a new sandbox\n204: - **THEN** the pod name SHALL be unique due to random suffix\n205: \n206: ---\n207: \n208: ### Requirement: Validation error handling\n209: \n210: The system SHALL validate request parameters and return appropriate errors.\n211: \n212: #### Scenario: Missing name validation\n213: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with empty `Name`\n214: - **WHEN** processing the request\n215: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n216: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"name\"`\n217: \n218: #### Scenario: Missing runtimeName validation\n219: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with empty `RuntimeName`\n220: - **WHEN** processing the request\n221: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n222: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"runtimeName\"`\n223: \n224: #### Scenario: Invalid RuntimeKind validation\n225: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with `RuntimeKind=\"InvalidKind\"`\n226: - **WHEN** processing the request\n227: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n228: - AND `Details.field` SHALL be `\"runtimeKind\"`\n229: \n230: #### Scenario: Runtime not found\n231: - **GIVEN** a `CreateSandboxRequest` with non-existent `RuntimeName`\n232: - **WHEN** processing the request\n233: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n234: \n235: ---\n236: \n237: ### Requirement: Sandbox retrieval\n238: \n239: The system SHALL retrieve sandbox pod information.\n240: \n241: #### Scenario: Get sandbox by name\n242: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n243: - **WHEN** processing the request\n244: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list pods with label selector `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime={runtimeName}`\n245: - AND return `SandboxResponse` for the matching pod\n246: \n247: #### Scenario: Sandbox not found\n248: - **GIVEN** a GET request for a non-existent sandbox\n249: - **WHEN** processing the request\n250: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n251: \n252: #### Scenario: List sandboxes\n253: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes`\n254: - **WHEN** processing the request\n255: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list all pods with label selector containing `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type`\n256: - AND return `SandboxListResponse` with all matching pods\n257: \n258: #### Scenario: List sandboxes by runtime\n259: - **GIVEN** a GET request to `/api/v1/sandboxes?runtimeName={runtimeName}`\n260: - **WHEN** processing the request\n261: - **THEN** the handler SHALL list pods with label selector `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime={runtimeName}`\n262: \n263: ---\n264: \n265: ### Requirement: Sandbox deletion\n266: \n267: The system SHALL delete sandbox pods.\n268: \n269: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox\n270: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n271: - **WHEN** processing the request\n272: - **THEN** the handler SHALL find the pod by sandbox name\n273: - AND call `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n274: \n275: #### Scenario: Delete sandbox with grace period\n276: - **GIVEN** a DELETE request with query parameter `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n277: - **WHEN** processing the request\n278: - **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30\n279: \n280: #### Scenario: Sandbox deletion updates session annotation\n281: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being deleted\n282: - **WHEN** the pod is found before deletion\n283: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n284: - AND the pod SHALL be updated before deletion\n285: \n286: ---\n287: \n288: ### Requirement: Warm pool handling for CodeInterpreter\n289: \n290: The system SHALL support warm pool management for CodeInterpreter sandboxes.\n291: \n292: #### Scenario: Check warm pool availability\n293: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `WarmPoolSize > 0`\n294: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n295: - **THEN** the handler SHALL check for available warm pool pods with annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member=true`\n296: \n297: #### Scenario: Use warm pool pod\n298: - **GIVEN** an available warm pool pod exists\n299: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n300: - **THEN** the handler SHALL update the warm pool pod instead of creating a new pod\n301: - AND remove `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` annotation\n302: - AND set `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` label\n303: \n304: #### Scenario: Warm pool pod not available\n305: - **GIVEN** no warm pool pod is available\n306: - **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n307: - **THEN** the handler SHALL create a new pod normally\n308: \n309: #### Scenario: Warm pool annotation for new pods\n310: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter sandbox pod created outside warm pool usage\n311: - **WHEN** the pod is created\n312: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/warm-pool-member` SHALL NOT be set\n313: \n314: ---\n315: \n316: ### Requirement: Port configuration\n317: \n318: The system SHALL configure container ports based on TargetPort definitions.\n319: \n320: #### Scenario: Add container ports\n321: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `Spec.Ports []TargetPort`\n322: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n323: - **THEN** each `TargetPort` SHALL be mapped to a `corev1.ContainerPort` in the pod spec\n324: \n325: #### Scenario: Port name from TargetPort\n326: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Name=\"http\"`\n327: - **WHEN** creating the container port\n328: - **THEN** the `corev1.ContainerPort.Name` SHALL be set to `\"http\"`\n329: \n330: #### Scenario: Port number from TargetPort\n331: - **GIVEN** a `TargetPort` with `Port=8080`\n332: - **WHEN** creating the container port\n333: - **THEN** the `corev1.ContainerPort.ContainerPort` SHALL be set to `8080`\n334: \n335: ---\n336: \n337: ### Requirement: RuntimeClassName handling\n338: \n339: The system SHALL apply RuntimeClassName for sandbox pods.\n340: \n341: #### Scenario: RuntimeClassName from CodeInterpreter template\n342: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.RuntimeClassName=\" KataContainers\"`\n343: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n344: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.RuntimeClassName` SHALL be set to `\"KataContainers\"`\n345: \n346: #### Scenario: RuntimeClassName nil handling\n347: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.RuntimeClassName` nil\n348: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n349: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.RuntimeClassName` SHALL NOT be set\n350: \n351: ---\n352: \n353: ### Requirement: Image configuration for CodeInterpreter\n354: \n355: The system SHALL configure container image for CodeInterpreter sandboxes.\n356: \n357: #### Scenario: Image from template\n358: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Image=\"python:3.11\"`\n359: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n360: - **THEN** the container image SHALL be `\"python:3.11\"`\n361: \n362: #### Scenario: ImagePullPolicy from template\n363: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.ImagePullPolicy=\"Always\"`\n364: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n365: - **THEN** the container `ImagePullPolicy` SHALL be `corev1.PullPolicy(\"Always\")`\n366: \n367: #### Scenario: ImagePullSecrets from template\n368: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.ImagePullSecrets`\n369: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n370: - **THEN** `Pod.Spec.ImagePullSecrets` SHALL be set from template\n371: \n372: ---\n373: \n374: ### Requirement: Environment variables handling\n375: \n376: The system SHALL apply environment variables from template.\n377: \n378: #### Scenario: Environment variables from CodeInterpreter template\n379: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Environment []corev1.EnvVar`\n380: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n381: - **THEN** the container `Env` SHALL include all environment variables from template\n382: \n383: #### Scenario: Environment variables merge\n384: - **GIVEN** system environment variables and template environment variables\n385: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n386: - **THEN** template environment variables SHALL be appended after system environment variables\n387: \n388: ---\n389: \n390: ### Requirement: Resource requirements handling\n391: \n392: The system SHALL apply resource requirements from template.\n393: \n394: #### Scenario: Resources from CodeInterpreter template\n395: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Resources` containing limits and requests\n396: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n397: - **THEN** the container `Resources` SHALL be set from template\n398: \n399: #### Scenario: Default resources when not specified\n400: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `Template.Resources`\n401: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n402: - **THEN** default resource limits SHALL NOT be applied (let Kubernetes defaults apply)\n403: \n404: ---\n405: \n406: ### Requirement: Command and Args handling\n407: \n408: The system SHALL apply command and args from template.\n409: \n410: #### Scenario: Command from template\n411: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Command=[\"python\", \"-m\"]`\n412: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n413: - **THEN** the container `Command` SHALL be set to `[\"python\", \"-m\"]`\n414: \n415: #### Scenario: Args from template\n416: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `Template.Args=[\"--port\", \"8080\"]`\n417: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n418: - **THEN** the container `Args` SHALL be set to `[\"--port\", \"8080\"]`\n419: \n420: #### Scenario: Empty Command and Args\n421: - **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with empty `Command` and `Args`\n422: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox pod\n423: - **THEN** the container SHALL use the default entrypoint from the image\n424: \n425: ---\n426: \n427: ### Requirement: Session management\n428: \n429: The system SHALL manage session lifecycle annotations.\n430: \n431: #### Scenario: Session start timestamp\n432: - **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being created for a session\n433: - **WHEN** the pod is created\n434: - **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` SHALL be set\n435: \n436: #### Scenario: Session timeout calculation\n437: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `SessionTimeout=15m`\n438: - **WHEN** calculating session expiration\n439: - **THEN** the expiration time SHALL be `sessionStart + SessionTimeout`\n440: \n441: #### Scenario: Max session duration calculation\n442: - **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration=8h`\n443: - **WHEN** calculating maximum session expiration\n444: - **THEN** the maximum expiration time SHALL be `sessionStart + MaxSessionDuration`\n445: \n446: ---\n447: \n448: ### Requirement: Error handling and responses\n449: \n450: The system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors appropriately.\n451: \n452: #### Scenario: Kubernetes API error\n453: - **GIVEN** a Kubernetes API call returns an error\n454: - **WHEN** processing the sandbox request\n455: - **THEN** the error SHALL be wrapped in `InternalError`\n456: - AND response SHALL be HTTP 500 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"INTERNAL_ERROR\"`\n457: \n458: #### Scenario: Pod already exists\n459: - **GIVEN** a pod with the same name already exists\n460: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox\n461: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 409 Conflict\n462: - AND `ErrorResponse.Code` SHALL be `\"CONFLICT\"`\n463: \n464: #### Scenario: Namespace not found\n465: - **GIVEN** the target namespace does not exist\n466: - **WHEN** creating the sandbox\n467: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n468: \n469: ---\n470: \n471: ### Requirement: Request context usage\n472: \n473: The system SHALL use request context for API calls.\n474: \n475: #### Scenario: Context propagation\n476: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with context\n477: - **WHEN** making Kubernetes API calls\n478: - **THEN** `r.Context()` SHALL be used as the context parameter\n479: \n480: #### Scenario: Context timeout handling\n481: - **GIVEN** a request context that times out\n482: - **WHEN** the Kubernetes API call is in progress\n483: - **THEN** the API call SHALL be cancelled\n484: - AND response SHALL be HTTP 503 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE\"`\n485: \n486: ---\n487: \n488: ### Requirement: JSON request parsing\n489: \n490: The system SHALL parse JSON request body correctly.\n491: \n492: #### Scenario: Valid JSON parsing\n493: - **GIVEN** a POST request with valid JSON body\n494: - **WHEN** parsing the request\n495: - **THEN** `json.NewDecoder(r.Body).Decode(&req)` SHALL be used\n496: - AND request body SHALL be closed\n497: \n498: #### Scenario: Invalid JSON parsing\n499: - **GIVEN** a POST request with invalid JSON body\n500: - **WHEN** parsing the request\n501: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n502: - AND `Details.reason` SHALL indicate JSON parsing failure\n503: \n504: ---\n505: \n506: ### Requirement: JSON response writing\n507: \n508: The system SHALL write JSON responses correctly.\n509: \n510: #### Scenario: Success response\n511: - **GIVEN** a successful sandbox creation\n512: - **WHEN** writing the response\n513: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 201 Created\n514: - AND `Content-Type` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n515: - AND body SHALL be `SandboxResponse` JSON\n516: \n517: #### Scenario: List response\n518: - **GIVEN** a successful sandbox list\n519: - **WHEN** writing the response\n520: - **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 200 OK\n521: - AND body SHALL be `SandboxListResponse` JSON\n522: \n523: ---\n524: \n525: ### Requirement: Unit tests\n526: \n527: The system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for SandboxHandler.\n528: \n529: #### Scenario: CreateSandboxRequest validation tests\n530: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n531: - **WHEN** running tests\n532: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n533:   - Missing name returns 400\n534:   - Missing runtimeName returns 400\n535:   - Invalid RuntimeKind returns 400\n536:   - Valid request passes validation\n537: \n538: #### Scenario: Label application tests\n539: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n540: - **WHEN** running tests\n541: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n542:   - Owner runtime label is applied\n543:   - Owner kind label is applied\n544:   - Sandbox type label is correct for AgentRuntime\n545:   - Sandbox type label is correct for CodeInterpreter\n546:   - Template labels are merged correctly\n547: \n548: #### Scenario: Annotation application tests\n549: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n550: - **WHEN** running tests\n551: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n552:   - Session start annotation is applied\n553:   - Last activity annotation is applied\n554:   - Auth mode annotation is applied for CodeInterpreter\n555: \n556: #### Scenario: Pod creation tests\n557: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n558: - **WHEN** running tests\n559: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n560:   - Pod is created with correct spec from AgentRuntime template\n561:   - Pod is created with correct spec from CodeInterpreter template\n562:   - Pod name follows naming convention\n563: \n564: #### Scenario: Warm pool tests\n565: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n566: - **WHEN** running tests\n567: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n568:   - Warm pool pod is reused when available\n569:   - New pod is created when warm pool not available\n570:   - Warm pool annotation is removed on reuse\n571: \n572: ---\n573: \n574: ### Requirement: Integration tests\n575: \n576: The system SHALL have integration tests with fake Kubernetes clients.\n577: \n578: #### Scenario: Full sandbox creation flow\n579: - **GIVEN** a fake clientset with AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter CRDs\n580: - **WHEN** running integration tests\n581: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify complete sandbox creation from request to pod creation\n582: \n583: #### Scenario: End-to-end API test\n584: - **GIVEN** a running HTTPServer with SandboxHandler\n585: - **WHEN** sending POST request to `/api/v1/sandboxes`\n586: - **THEN** tests SHALL verify correct HTTP response and pod creation\n587: \n588: ---\n589: \n590: ### Requirement: Directory structure\n591: \n592: The system SHALL organize sandbox handler files correctly.\n593: \n594: #### Scenario: Sandbox handler file location\n595: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n596: - **WHEN** listing files\n597: - **THEN** `sandbox.go` SHALL exist with `SandboxHandler` implementation\n598: \n599: #### Scenario: Sandbox handler test file location\n600: - **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`\n601: - **WHEN** listing files\n602: - **THEN** `sandbox_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n603: \n604: ---\n605: \n606: ## Implementation Files\n607: \n608: | File | Purpose |\n609: |------|---------|\n610: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go` | SandboxHandler implementation |\n611: | `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go` | SandboxHandler unit tests |\n612: \n613: ---\n614: \n615: ## Dependencies\n616: \n617: | Package | Purpose |\n618: |---------|---------|\n619: | `client-go/clientset/versioned` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter typed client |\n620: | `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n621: | `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod, Container types |\n622: | `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ObjectMeta, ListOptions, CreateOptions |\n623: | `encoding/json` | Request/Response JSON handling |\n624: | `time` | Timestamp handling for annotations |\n625: \n626: ---\n627: \n628: ## API Endpoints\n629: \n630: | Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n631: |----------|--------|---------|\n632: | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | POST | Create a new sandbox |\n633: | `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | GET | Get sandbox by name |\n634: | `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | DELETE | Delete sandbox |\n635: | `/api/v1/sandboxes` | GET | List sandboxes |\n636: \n637: ---\n638: \n639: ## Error Codes\n640: \n641: | Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n642: |------|-------------|-------------|\n643: | `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Invalid request parameter |\n644: | `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Runtime or sandbox not found |\n645: | `CONFLICT` | 409 | Pod already exists |\n646: | `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n647: | `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Context timeout or dependency unavailable |\n648: \n649: ---\n650: \n651: ## Label Keys Applied\n652: \n653: | Key | Value Source |\n654: |-----|--------------|\n655: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-runtime` | `RuntimeName` from request |\n656: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/owner-kind` | `RuntimeKind` from request |\n657: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/sandbox-type` | `\"agent\"` or `\"code-interpreter\"` |\n658: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-id` | `SessionID` from request |\n659: \n660: ---\n661: \n662: ## Annotation Keys Applied\n663: \n664: | Key | Value Source |\n665: |-----|--------------|\n666: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-start` | Current timestamp RFC3339 |\n667: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` | Current timestamp |\n668: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/auth-mode` | `CodeInterpreter.Spec.AuthMode` |\n669: | `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` | Current timestamp (on deletion) |\n670: \n671: ---\n672: \n673: ## Validation Checklist\n674: \n675: - [ ] SandboxHandler implements Handler interface\n676: - [ ] POST `/api/v1/sandboxes` creates pods correctly\n677: - [ ] GET `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` retrieves sandbox info\n678: - [ ] DELETE `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` deletes sandbox pod\n679: - [ ] GET `/api/v1/sandboxes` lists all sandboxes\n680: - [ ] Labels are applied according to shared_types.go constants\n681: - [ ] Annotations are applied correctly\n682: - [ ] Warm pool handling works for CodeInterpreter\n683: - [ ] Port configuration from TargetPort\n684: - [ ] RuntimeClassName handling\n685: - [ ] Environment variables from template\n686: - [ ] Resource requirements from template\n687: - [ ] Command and Args from template\n688: - [ ] Validation errors return correct HTTP status\n689: - [ ] Kubernetes API errors handled correctly\n690: - [ ] Context propagated to API calls\n691: - [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n692: - [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n693: - [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n694: - [ ] Integration tests pass\n\n(End of file - total 694 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Delta Spec: AR-005 — Sandbox 创建处理器\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox creation handler that processes sandbox creation requests for AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter resources, including pod creation, session management, status updates, and warm pool handling.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: SandboxHandler type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `SandboxHandler` as an HTTP handler for sandbox creation operations.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-005/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775844790190,"end":1775844790200}}}}
