{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844930976,"sessionID":"ses_287677128ffe1OYkAXjU0bM6jn","part":{"id":"prt_d789b353e001UisYllnEnvoiIm","messageID":"msg_d789966290013eiSnaQrEm4ewk","sessionID":"ses_287677128ffe1OYkAXjU0bM6jn","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-265c07d3c50f407391aeef3ad1c27525","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-006/delta-spec.md","content":"# Delta Spec: AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理\n\n**Module:** `pkg/workloadmanager`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nDefine the Sandbox lifecycle manager that handles sandbox deletion, TTL-based cleanup, idle timeout monitoring, max session duration enforcement, and integration with the Store interface for sandbox state persistence. This includes the garbage collector that runs periodically to clean up expired sandboxes.\n\n---\n\n## GIVEN/WHEN/THEN Scenarios\n\n### Requirement: LifecycleManager type definition\n\nThe system SHALL define `LifecycleManager` as a manager for sandbox lifecycle operations.\n\n#### Scenario: LifecycleManager struct definition\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `LifecycleManager` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `client clientset.Interface` for Kubernetes API access\n  - `kubeClient kubernetes.Interface` for core Kubernetes API\n  - `store Store` for sandbox state persistence\n  - `logger Logger` for structured logging\n  - `namespace string` for default namespace\n  - `gcInterval time.Duration` for garbage collection interval\n  - `stopCh chan struct{}` for stopping the manager\n\n#### Scenario: NewLifecycleManager constructor\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go`\n- **WHEN** calling `NewLifecycleManager(client clientset.Interface, kubeClient kubernetes.Interface, store Store, logger Logger, namespace string, gcInterval time.Duration)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `*LifecycleManager` with all fields initialized\n- AND `gcInterval` SHALL default to `GarbageCollectorInterval` if zero\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Store interface implementation\n\nThe system SHALL implement the `Store` interface for sandbox state persistence.\n\n#### Scenario: MemoryStore implementation\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `MemoryStore` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain:\n  - `mu sync.RWMutex` for thread-safe access\n  - `sandboxes map[string]*types.SandboxInfo` keyed by sessionID\n  - `expirationIndex map[string]time.Time` keyed by sandboxID for TTL tracking\n\n#### Scenario: StoreSandbox method\n- **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` instance\n- **WHEN** calling `StoreSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo)`\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be stored keyed by `sandbox.SessionID`\n- AND `expirationIndex` SHALL be updated with `sandbox.ExpiresAt`\n\n#### Scenario: GetSandboxBySessionID method\n- **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n- **WHEN** calling `GetSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `*types.SandboxInfo` if found\n- AND return `NotFoundError` if not found\n\n#### Scenario: UpdateSandbox method\n- **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n- **WHEN** calling `UpdateSandbox(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo)`\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be updated in the store\n- AND `expirationIndex` SHALL be updated if `ExpiresAt` changed\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxBySessionID method\n- **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n- **WHEN** calling `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx context.Context, sessionID string)`\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be removed from `sandboxes` map\n- AND the sandbox SHALL be removed from `expirationIndex` map\n\n#### Scenario: ListSandboxes method\n- **GIVEN** a `MemoryStore` with stored sandboxes\n- **WHEN** calling `ListSandboxes(ctx context.Context)`\n- **THEN** it SHALL return `[]*types.SandboxInfo` with all stored sandboxes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: LifecycleManager Start method\n\nThe system SHALL start the lifecycle manager with garbage collection loop.\n\n#### Scenario: Start begins garbage collection\n- **GIVEN** a `LifecycleManager` instance\n- **WHEN** calling `Start(ctx context.Context)`\n- **THEN** the garbage collection loop SHALL start\n- AND the loop SHALL run at `gcInterval` frequency\n\n#### Scenario: Stop stops garbage collection\n- **GIVEN** a running `LifecycleManager`\n- **WHEN** calling `Stop()`\n- **THEN** `stopCh` SHALL be closed\n- AND the garbage collection loop SHALL stop\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Garbage collection implementation\n\nThe system SHALL implement garbage collection for expired sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: GC checks expired sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** a `LifecycleManager` with `store` containing sandboxes\n- **WHEN** the garbage collection runs\n- **THEN** it SHALL check `expirationIndex` for expired entries\n- AND current time SHALL be compared against `ExpiresAt`\n\n#### Scenario: GC deletes expired sandbox pod\n- **GIVEN** an expired sandbox in the store\n- **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n- **THEN** `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})` SHALL be called\n- AND the sandbox SHALL be removed from the store\n\n#### Scenario: GC handles multiple expired sandboxes\n- **GIVEN** multiple expired sandboxes in the store\n- **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n- **THEN** all expired sandboxes SHALL be deleted in sequence\n- AND errors for individual deletions SHALL be logged but not stop the loop\n\n#### Scenario: GC logs deletion activity\n- **GIVEN** a garbage collection deletion\n- **WHEN** a sandbox is deleted\n- **THEN** `logger.Info` SHALL be called with sandbox ID and reason\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: TTL-based cleanup\n\nThe system SHALL enforce TTL-based cleanup for sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Default TTL value\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the constants\n- **THEN** `DefaultSandboxTTL` SHALL be `8 * time.Hour`\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox TTL from runtime spec\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `MaxSessionDuration=4h`\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the sandbox `ExpiresAt` SHALL be `CreatedAt + MaxSessionDuration`\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox TTL from CodeInterpreter spec\n- **GIVEN** a CodeInterpreter with `MaxSessionDuration=6h`\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the sandbox `ExpiresAt` SHALL be `CreatedAt + MaxSessionDuration`\n\n#### Scenario: TTL exceeded triggers deletion\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with `ExpiresAt` in the past\n- **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be marked for deletion\n- AND deletion reason SHALL be `ConditionReasonMaxDurationReached`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Idle timeout enforcement\n\nThe system SHALL enforce idle timeout for sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Default idle timeout value\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the constants\n- **THEN** `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout` SHALL be `15 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: Idle timeout from runtime spec\n- **GIVEN** an AgentRuntime with `SessionTimeout=30m`\n- **WHEN** creating a sandbox\n- **THEN** the idle timeout SHALL be derived from `SessionTimeout`\n\n#### Scenario: LastActivity tracking\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity`\n- **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n- **THEN** `LastActivity` SHALL be compared against current time\n- AND if `current - LastActivity > SessionTimeout`, sandbox SHALL be deleted\n\n#### Scenario: Idle timeout exceeded triggers deletion\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox with no activity for longer than `SessionTimeout`\n- **WHEN** garbage collection runs\n- **THEN** the sandbox SHALL be deleted\n- AND deletion reason SHALL be `ConditionReasonIdleTimeout`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: DeleteSandboxHandler implementation\n\nThe system SHALL implement the sandbox deletion handler.\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxHandler struct\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the handler struct\n- **THEN** `SandboxHandler` SHALL have method `DeleteSandbox(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) error`\n\n#### Scenario: DELETE endpoint registration\n- **GIVEN** `SandboxHandler.Register(r chi.Router)`\n- **WHEN** examining registered routes\n- **THEN** `DELETE /api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` SHALL be registered\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox by name\n- **GIVEN** a DELETE request to `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** the handler SHALL find the pod by sandbox name using label selector\n- AND call `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Delete(ctx, podName, metav1.DeleteOptions{})`\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox with grace period\n- **GIVEN** a DELETE request with query parameter `gracePeriodSeconds=30`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 30\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox updates store\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted via API\n- **WHEN** the pod deletion succeeds\n- **THEN** `store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID)` SHALL be called\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox sets session-end annotation\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod being deleted\n- **WHEN** the pod is found before deletion\n- **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set to current timestamp\n- AND the pod SHALL be updated with `Update` call before deletion\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox returns success\n- **GIVEN** a successful sandbox deletion\n- **WHEN** writing the response\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 200 OK\n- AND `Content-Type` SHALL be `\"application/json\"`\n- AND body SHALL be `SuccessResponse{Data: {\"deleted\": true, \"sandboxId\": \"<id>\"}}`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: DeleteSandboxRequest type\n\nThe system SHALL define request types for sandbox deletion API.\n\n#### Scenario: DeleteSandboxRequest struct\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the `DeleteSandboxRequest` struct\n- **THEN** the struct SHALL contain fields:\n  - `Name string` with JSON tag `name` (optional, can use URL path)\n  - `Force bool` with JSON tag `force` (optional, force delete)\n  - `GracePeriodSeconds int64` with JSON tag `gracePeriodSeconds` (optional)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Session end handling\n\nThe system SHALL properly handle session end transitions.\n\n#### Scenario: Session-end annotation on deletion\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with active session\n- **WHEN** the sandbox is deleted\n- **THEN** annotation `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` SHALL be set\n\n#### Scenario: Session-end annotation format\n- **GIVEN** a session-end annotation being set\n- **WHEN** setting the annotation value\n- **THEN** the value SHALL be RFC3339 formatted timestamp\n\n#### Scenario: Session-end updates pod before deletion\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted with grace period\n- **WHEN** updating the pod\n- **THEN** the pod SHALL be updated with `kubeClient.CoreV1().Pods(namespace).Update(ctx, pod, metav1.UpdateOptions{})`\n- AND the deletion SHALL proceed after update\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: NotFoundError handling\n\nThe system SHALL handle not found errors for sandbox operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox not found on delete\n- **GIVEN** a DELETE request for non-existent sandbox\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 404 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"NOT_FOUND\"`\n- AND `Message` SHALL indicate sandbox not found\n\n#### Scenario: Sandbox not found in store\n- **GIVEN** a `GetSandboxBySessionID` call for non-existent session\n- **WHEN** the call executes\n- **THEN** `NotFoundError{Resource: \"sandbox\", Name: sessionID}` SHALL be returned\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Force deletion\n\nThe system SHALL support force deletion of sandboxes.\n\n#### Scenario: Force delete bypasses grace period\n- **GIVEN** a DELETE request with `force=true`\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** `DeleteOptions.GracePeriodSeconds` SHALL be set to 0\n\n#### Scenario: Force delete removes finalizers\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox pod with finalizers\n- **WHEN** force deleting\n- **THEN** finalizers SHALL be removed before deletion\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Deletion validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate deletion requests.\n\n#### Scenario: Name required for delete\n- **GIVEN** a DELETE request without name in path\n- **WHEN** processing the request\n- **THEN** response SHALL be HTTP 400 with `ErrorResponse.Code=\"VALIDATION_ERROR\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Lifecycle status tracking\n\nThe system SHALL track sandbox lifecycle status.\n\n#### Scenario: SandboxInfo status field\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/common/types/sandbox.go`\n- **WHEN** reading `SandboxInfo`\n- **THEN** `Status` field SHALL be present with JSON tag `status`\n\n#### Scenario: Status values\n- **GIVEN** sandbox lifecycle transitions\n- **WHEN** updating status\n- **THEN** valid values SHALL include:\n  - `\"creating\"` - sandbox being created\n  - `\"running\"` - sandbox active\n  - `\"expiring\"` - sandbox approaching TTL\n  - `\"idle\"` - sandbox idle timeout approaching\n  - `\"terminating\"` - sandbox being deleted\n  - `\"terminated\"` - sandbox deleted\n\n#### Scenario: Status update on deletion\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox being deleted\n- **WHEN** deletion begins\n- **THEN** status SHALL be updated to `\"terminating\"`\n\n#### Scenario: Status update after deletion\n- **GIVEN** a sandbox deleted successfully\n- **WHEN** deletion completes\n- **THEN** status SHALL be updated to `\"terminated\"`\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Error handling for lifecycle operations\n\nThe system SHALL handle Kubernetes API errors during lifecycle operations.\n\n#### Scenario: Pod deletion error\n- **GIVEN** a pod deletion that returns error\n- **WHEN** garbage collection or delete handler executes\n- **THEN** error SHALL be logged\n- AND `InternalError` SHALL be returned for API calls\n\n#### Scenario: Pod update error before delete\n- **GIVEN** a pod update that fails before deletion\n- **WHEN** setting session-end annotation\n- **THEN** the error SHALL be logged\n- AND deletion SHALL proceed anyway (annotation update is non-blocking)\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Concurrent deletion safety\n\nThe system SHALL handle concurrent deletion requests safely.\n\n#### Scenario: Same sandbox deleted concurrently\n- **GIVEN** two delete requests for the same sandbox\n- **WHEN** both requests execute\n- **THEN** only one SHALL succeed\n- AND the second SHALL receive 404 Not Found or 409 Conflict\n\n#### Scenario: Store deletion thread safety\n- **GIVEN** `MemoryStore` with concurrent operations\n- **WHEN** multiple goroutines access the store\n- **THEN** `sync.RWMutex` SHALL protect all map operations\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: GC interval configuration\n\nThe system SHALL allow configurable garbage collection interval.\n\n#### Scenario: Default GC interval\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go`\n- **WHEN** reading the constants\n- **THEN** `GarbageCollectorInterval` SHALL be `2 * time.Minute`\n\n#### Scenario: Custom GC interval\n- **GIVEN** `NewLifecycleManager` with `gcInterval=5m`\n- **WHEN** creating the manager\n- **THEN** garbage collection SHALL run every 5 minutes\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for LifecycleManager\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for lifecycle management.\n\n#### Scenario: LifecycleManager creation test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - NewLifecycleManager returns valid instance\n  - Default gcInterval is applied\n\n#### Scenario: GC loop test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Start begins the GC loop\n  - Stop terminates the GC loop\n\n#### Scenario: TTL cleanup test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Expired sandboxes are detected\n  - Expired sandboxes are deleted from store and Kubernetes\n\n#### Scenario: Idle timeout test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Idle sandboxes are detected\n  - Idle sandboxes are deleted\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for MemoryStore\n\nThe system SHALL have comprehensive unit tests for MemoryStore.\n\n#### Scenario: Store CRUD test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - StoreSandbox stores sandbox correctly\n  - GetSandboxBySessionID returns correct sandbox\n  - UpdateSandbox updates sandbox correctly\n  - DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes sandbox\n  - ListSandboxes returns all sandboxes\n\n#### Scenario: Store concurrency test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Concurrent StoreSandbox operations are safe\n  - Concurrent Get and Delete operations are safe\n\n#### Scenario: NotFound error test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - GetSandboxBySessionID returns NotFoundError for missing sandbox\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Unit tests for DeleteSandbox handler\n\nThe system SHALL have unit tests for sandbox deletion handler.\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox success test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - DELETE returns 200 on success\n  - Pod is deleted from Kubernetes\n  - Sandbox is removed from store\n\n#### Scenario: Delete sandbox not found test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - DELETE returns 404 for non-existent sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: Grace period test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - GracePeriodSeconds is applied to DeleteOptions\n\n#### Scenario: Force delete test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Force=true sets GracePeriodSeconds=0\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Integration tests for lifecycle\n\nThe system SHALL have integration tests for lifecycle management.\n\n#### Scenario: Full lifecycle flow test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Sandbox creation stores in MemoryStore\n  - TTL expiration triggers deletion\n  - Store reflects deleted sandbox\n\n#### Scenario: Concurrent lifecycle test\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n- **WHEN** running tests\n- **THEN** tests SHALL verify:\n  - Multiple sandboxes handled concurrently\n  - No race conditions\n\n---\n\n### Requirement: Directory structure\n\nThe system SHALL organize lifecycle files correctly.\n\n#### Scenario: Lifecycle file location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `lifecycle.go` SHALL exist with `LifecycleManager` implementation\n\n#### Scenario: Lifecycle test file location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `lifecycle_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n\n#### Scenario: Store file location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `store.go` SHALL exist with `MemoryStore` implementation\n\n#### Scenario: Store test file location\n- **GIVEN** `pkg/workloadmanager/`\n- **WHEN** listing files\n- **THEN** `store_test.go` SHALL exist with unit tests\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Files\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle.go` | LifecycleManager implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/lifecycle_test.go` | LifecycleManager unit tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/store.go` | MemoryStore implementation |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/store_test.go` | MemoryStore unit tests |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/sandbox.go` | DeleteSandbox handler (extends AR-005) |\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|\n| `client-go/clientset/versioned` | AgentRuntime and CodeInterpreter typed client |\n| `k8s.io/client-go/kubernetes` | Core Kubernetes API client |\n| `k8s.io/api/core/v1` | Pod types |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1` | ObjectMeta, DeleteOptions |\n| `sync` | Thread-safe store operations |\n| `time` | TTL and interval handling |\n| `context` | Context propagation |\n\n---\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Purpose |\n|----------|--------|---------|\n| `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}` | DELETE | Delete sandbox by name |\n\n---\n\n## Error Codes\n\n| Code | HTTP Status | Description |\n|------|-------------|-------------|\n| `VALIDATION_ERROR` | 400 | Missing or invalid parameters |\n| `NOT_FOUND` | 404 | Sandbox not found |\n| `INTERNAL_ERROR` | 500 | Kubernetes API error |\n| `SERVICE_UNAVAILABLE` | 503 | Lifecycle manager not running |\n\n---\n\n## Deletion Reasons\n\n| Reason | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `IdleTimeout` | Sandbox deleted due to idle timeout exceeded |\n| `MaxDurationReached` | Sandbox deleted due to max session duration exceeded |\n| `UserRequest` | Sandbox deleted via DELETE API request |\n\n---\n\n## Annotation Keys for Lifecycle\n\n| Key | Value Source |\n|-----|--------------|\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/session-end` | Current timestamp on deletion |\n| `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/last-activity` | Updated on each activity |\n\n---\n\n## Sandbox Status Values\n\n| Status | Description |\n|--------|-------------|\n| `creating` | Sandbox pod being created |\n| `running` | Sandbox active and serving |\n| `expiring` | Approaching TTL expiration |\n| `idle` | Approaching idle timeout |\n| `terminating` | Sandbox being deleted |\n| `terminated` | Sandbox deleted |\n\n---\n\n## Validation Checklist\n\n- [ ] LifecycleManager struct defined with all required fields\n- [ ] NewLifecycleManager constructor initializes all fields\n- [ ] MemoryStore implements Store interface\n- [ ] StoreSandbox stores sandbox keyed by sessionID\n- [ ] GetSandboxBySessionID returns sandbox or NotFoundError\n- [ ] UpdateSandbox updates sandbox and expiration index\n- [ ] DeleteSandboxBySessionID removes from both maps\n- [ ] ListSandboxes returns all sandboxes\n- [ ] Start begins garbage collection loop\n- [ ] Stop terminates garbage collection loop\n- [ ] GC checks expirationIndex for expired entries\n- [ ] TTL exceeded triggers deletion with MaxDurationReached reason\n- [ ] Idle timeout exceeded triggers deletion with IdleTimeout reason\n- [ ] DELETE endpoint registered at `/api/v1/sandboxes/{name}`\n- [ ] GracePeriodSeconds query parameter applied\n- [ ] Force delete sets GracePeriodSeconds=0\n- [ ] Session-end annotation set before deletion\n- [ ] Store updated on successful deletion\n- [ ] NotFound handling for missing sandbox\n- [ ] Concurrent deletion handled safely\n- [ ] Status tracking for lifecycle transitions\n- [ ] Pass `go vet` with zero issues\n- [ ] Pass `golangci-lint` with zero issues\n- [ ] Unit tests pass with >80% coverage\n- [ ] Integration tests pass"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.\n\nLSP errors detected in other files:\n<diagnostics file=\"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/workloadmanager/informers_test.go\">\nERROR [78:2] expected declaration, found informers\n</diagnostics>","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/common/types/sandbox.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":59,"character":40},"end":{"line":59,"character":71}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription"